HEADWORD: Remontant
<hw>Re*mon"tant</hw> <pr>(-t<it>a</it>nt)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos><ety>[F.]</ety> <fld>(Hort.)</fld> <def>Rising again; --
applied to a class of roses which bloom more than once in a season; the
hybrid perpetual roses, of which the Jacqueminot is a well-known
example.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

